</b>146.150.<b> Take steps to address increasing trends in early, forced and child 
marriage (Sierra Leone); 
</b>146.151.<b> Adopt proper measures in order to discourage the practice of early 
and forced marriages (Italy); 
</b>146.152.<b> Revise Malaysia&#8217;s legislative framework in order to ensure freedom 
of religion or belief for all (Italy); 
</b>146.153.<b> Take concrete steps to implement its commitment to promote and 
protect the rights of all people to worship in peace and security without 
discrimination or restriction (Canada); 
</b>146.154.<b> Continue its efforts to promote inter-religious dialogues and reconcile 
different schools of Islamic thoughts and other religions (Sudan); 
</b>146.155.<b> Continue efforts and engage in a structured interfaith dialogue, 
including religious minorities (Austria); 
</b>146.156.<b> Take measures to ensure that all persons, including Muslims, can 
freely exercise their right to freedom of religion and belief, without interference 
by the state and including the right to change their religion (Austria); 
</b>146.157.<b> Bring the Printing Presses and Publication Act (1984), the Official 
Secrets Act (1972) and the Sedition Act (1948) in line with international human 
